.section.grid
  %a{:name=>"speakers"}
    %h2 Who
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/hamptoncatlin.jpg"}
    %a{:name=>"hampton"}
      %h3 Host: Hampton Catlin
    .bio
      Hampton is the creator of Sass. He also thinks he's pretty funny. He wrote this in the third person. He's the CTO of Moovweb and also the creator of #{link_to "Haml", "http://haml.info/", :target=>"_blank"}, Tritium, and Wikipedia Mobile.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/chriseppstein.jpg"}
    %a{:name=>"chris"}
      %h3 Keynote: Chris Eppstein
    .bio
      Chris is the creator of #{link_to "Compass", "http://compass-style.org", :target=>"_blank"}, and is a Sass Core Team Member and Chief Instigator. Chris Eppstein is an open source hacker at #{link_to "LinkedIn", "http://www.linkedin.com/", :target=>"_blank"}, and probably the nicest person you'll ever meet. Seriously. So freaking nice.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/claudinasarahe.jpeg"}
    %a{:name=>"claudina"} 
      %h3 Claudina Sarahe
    .bio
      Claudina is a front-end developer at #{link_to "Oddbird", "http://oddbird.net/", :target=>"_blank"} and Radical. She's also one of the organizers of #{link_to "SassConf", "http://sassconf.com/", :target=>"_blank"} and is one of those people that everyone wishes they could be friends with. She's that cool.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/smithschwartz.jpg"}
    %a{:name=>"smith"} 
      %h3 Smith Schwartz
    .bio
      Smith started her career in the world of musuem experience design in Chicago. Then she got bit by the front-end bug and now travels the world, freelancing and building awesome stuff. She gives fantastic advice and is currently being sucked into the technical vortex called San Francisco.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/aaronleung.png"}
    %a{:name=>"aaron"} 
      %h3 Aaron Leung
    .bio
      Aaron is the maintainer of #{link_to "LibSass", "http://libsass.org/",   :target=>"_blank"}, the C++ implementation of Sass. He'll be talking   about upcoming features in this implementation. In his spare time he is learning Norwegian.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/divyamanian.jpeg"}
    %a{:name=>"divya"} 
      %h3 Divya Manian
    .bio
      Divya is the goddess of new CSS features and a product manager at Adobe. She is also known for #{link_to "HTML5 Please", "http://html5please.com/", :target=>"_blank"}, #{link_to "HTML5 Boilerplate", "http://html5boilerplate.com/", :target=>"_blank"}, #{link_to "w3 Fools", "http://www.w3fools.com/", :target=>"_blank"}, and #{link_to "Move the Web Forward", "http://movethewebforward.org/", :target=>"_blank"}.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/dalesande.png"}
    %a{:name=>"dale"}
      %h3 Dale Sande
    .bio
      Dale is a UX designer who started the first ever Sass Meetup in Seattle. A true Sass evangelist, he also runs the SassCast podcast and created #{link_to "SassMeister", "http://sassmeister.com/", :target=>"_blank"}.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/ericsuzanne.png"}
    %a{:name=>"eric"}
      %h3 Eric M. Suzanne
    .bio
      Eric is an artist and experience designer who created the exemplary Sass library #{link_to "Susy", "http://susy.oddbird.net/", :target=>"_blank"}. He is a partner at #{link_to "Oddbird", "http://oddbird.net/", :target=>"_blank"} and regularly contributes to Compass.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/elyseholladay.jpeg"}
    %a{:name=>"elyse"}
      %h3 Elyse Holladay
    .bio
      Elyse is a teacher, speaker and front-end developer at #{link_to "MakerSquare", "http://www.themakersquare.com", :target=>"_blank"}. She's passionate about Sass and designing in the browser. She has a gif ready for any occasion, so be prepared for a gif-tastic presentation.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/cliffseal.jpeg"}
    %a{:name=>"cliff"}
      %h3 Cliff Seal
    .bio
      Cliff is a Senior UX Architect at #{link_to "Pardot", "http://www.pardot.com", :target=>"_blank"}, co-founded #{link_to "MusicGrid", "http://musicgrid.me/", :target=>"_blank"}, develops for Wordpress, and does countless other things. He's eager to talk about the balance between best practices with what users want.
  .unit.one-of-two
    .pic
      %img{:src=>"images/speakers/joelencioni.jpeg"}
    %a{:name=>"joe"}
      %h3 Joe Lencioni
    .bio
      Joe is a web developer and designer who works at #{link_to "Causes", "http://www.causes.com", :target=>"_blank"}. Along with #{link_to "Henric Trotzig", "http://twitter.com/henrictrotzig", :target=>"_blank"}, he will be presenting a cool new open-source project to help manage stylesheet changes.
